name: Zendesk_HTTP_Connector
description: This IVR flow gets user information from Zendesk CRM using ANI and then gets ticket details using user ID

properties.description: Queue to Agent
properties.name: QueueContact

properties.description: Music in Queue
properties.name: PlayMusic

properties.description: Plays Welcome Message
properties.name: Greeting

promptsTts.value:
Greetings, Welcome to IVR !
Give us a moment to fetch your details.

properties.description: This activity looks up a user based on the ANI
properties.name: LookupUser

properties.description: This is the main menu.
properties.name: MainMenu

promptsTts.value:
Press 1 to connect to an agent.
Press 2 to disconnect this call.

properties.httpRequestBody: {"ticket": {"comment": { "body": "Ticket update | Customer called to check the status of the ticket." }}}
properties.description: Post Comments to the last created ticket
properties.name: PostComments
CallDisconnect
properties.description: This disconnects the call with the user.

properties.name: ConditionCheck
properties.description: This condition is to check the value of Ticket ID from the last HTTP request.
Plays no ticket found information to the customer.
properties.name: PlayTicketDetails_NoTicket

promptsTts.value:
Hello, {{userName}} !
It looks like there is no Open ticket associated with your number. Let me transfer your call to one of our agents to assist you today.

properties.description: Plays ticket details to the customer.
properties.name: PlayTicketDetails

promptsTts.value:
Hello, {{userName}} !
I see, a ticket was created for you recently.
Your ticket number {{ticketID}} is {{ticketStatus}}. 
Our team is still working on your ticket. Please wait for 48 hours for us to provide you the resolution.

properties.description: Looks up the Ticket details using the User ID
